es. The book reveals the need for self-expression of one’s own attitudes observable in contemporary spirituality, as well as the increasing participation of believers in the development of their religious life and thus in the formation of their own religious identity. All these processes are interpreted in terms of performance theory. Applying this approach makes it possible to capture the believers’ need for activity and creativity in the field of practices alternative to the liturgy.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aChristianityzPoland. 0aPassion-playsxHistory and criticism. 0aReligious drama. 4aAufführung. 4aKatholizismus. 4aPassionsspiele. 4areligiöse Erfahrung. 7aRELIGION / Christianity / History.2bisacsh  aCatholicism.  aPassion plays.  aperformance.  areligious experience.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2017 Part 1z978311076249508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017z978311062526408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theology, Relig. Studies, Jewish Studies 2017z9783110548259oZDB-23-DGF0 cEPUBz97831105390660 cprintz978311053905940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311053996740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110539967423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110539967/original  a978-3-11-062526-4  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017b2017  a978-3-11-071954-3  DG Plus eBook-Package 2017b2017  a978-3-11-076249-5  DG Plus DeG Package 2017 Part 1b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL